    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Corbin Carroll** serving as our anchor; his 81.24 score is a direct result of batting second against a high-skill matchup and a favorable xwOBA environment. **Tyler Soderstrom** offers the highest leverage among our corner infielders at 76.91, benefiting immensely from a soft matchup against Erick Fedde and the optimal #4 lineup spot. Meanwhile, **James Wood** provides the most intriguing upside at the top of the order; despite the threat of an elite arm behind the plate, his #1 batting slot and +11% SP skill adjustment push his output to a robust 73.32, keeping him locked into our outfield.\n\nThe optimizer\u2019s most difficult choice involved **Seiya Suzuki**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a 51.44 score. While his base projections are generally sound, the combination of a high-skill arm in Freddy Peralta and a documented BvP disadvantage (27 PA) forced him to the bench in favor of the platoon-advantaged **Jose Caballero**, whose dynamic platoon edge against the opposing lefty creates a safer floor for our SB-starved squad. We are also closely monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters, particularly **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland**, as their value is sensitive to any potential move down the order against Ryan Feltner. While the wind-in factor at several venues is suppressing ceilings\u2014most notably for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Giancarlo Stanton**\u2014the matchup against soft contact pitchers keeps our core in the \"Strong\" start category across the board.",
